Aurora Borealis - the first in this Labradorite collection. Wrapped in Antique patina Copper. Price: $100. Comes with free Canada shipping and free matching cord. The flash on the main stone (10 carat Labradorite) is breathtaking and the accent stone (1 carat faceted Fluorite) sparkles in the Sun 💙💚💙
According to an ancient Inuit legend, long ago the Northern Lights were trapped inside the rocks along the coast of Labrador.  They were found by an Inuit warrior who tried to free them with his spear.  He couldn’t release of all the lights and so some remained imprisoned in the stones.  It is said tthat this is why labradorite is found in the rocks of Labrador today

Orgonite Ice test! 🙏🌬❄🕉
I have been messing around with making orgonite for about a month now, and I'm so happy with the way things are going so far! I froze 3 different pieces in regular tap water and this was the result! These pieces really art that complicated and yet they still had very impressive results! 
These are the diffrent orgonite pieces seen in the video: 
1) neodymium/copper/Amethyst pendant

2) shungite/obsidian/copper cone 
3) piezoelectric Quartz Octagon with copper and neodymium

Thanks for Looking!🙏
